Jdbc Template:
   - Removes boiler plate of code.
   - Opening and closing of connections will be taken care by framework.
   - it has the capabilities to map bean to a query result

We will create a datasource bean here, the inputs for that bean are
  - URL
  - Username
  - Password
  - Driver

- JdbcTemplate
- NamedParameterJDBCTemplate

-- Dependecies --
     <dependency>
         <groupId>org.springframework</groupId>
         <artifactId>spring-jdbc</artifactId>
         <version>${spring.version}</version>
     </dependency>
     <dependency>
         <groupId>org.postgresql</groupId>
         <artifactId>postgresql</artifactId>
         <version>42.2.9</version>
     </dependency>
